            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Orchids The International School - Pradhikaran,Nigdi"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Jaya Kas"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-04-16",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I would like to share my thoughts and experience regarding recent hike in school fees that has been implemented by school. As a parent, I was shocked to disappointed to learn about the sudden and significant increase in fees. At the time of admission, a fee structure was shared and told that there would be grade wise hike every year which is fine and reflects in the fee structure shared with me. However, three year later they have come up with a new fee structure and and enforced it for new and Old admissions as well, which makes substantial difference for old admissions. It comes to around 17 to 20 percent hike.\n\nThe concern is raised with school and the response is \"Grade wise hike would always be there and apart from this we had hiked fee after three years and no changes can be done\".\n\nI have never been informed during admission that there would be a separate hike apart from grade wise hike.\n\nThe way they have implemented is just Unfair and Unreasonable.\nIt creates a high financial burden. Who would receive a hike of 15 or more percent in salary ?\n\nIt should have been implemented only for new admissions.\n\nMy advise who are willing to take admission, please take confirmation that the fees structure being shared with them remains same for the whole tenure of the student in school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
      ]
